## V2H: The More Practical Near-Term Option?

While V2G (exporting to the grid) involves regulatory complexity and uncertain economics, **V2H (vehicle-to-home)** may be the more practical and immediate use case:

- **Use your car as a home battery** — Charge cheaply overnight, then power your home during peak hours. No grid export, no DNO complexity.
- **Backup power** — The Wallbox Quasar 2's "blackout mode" can keep essential circuits running during a power cut. With 60–80kWh of battery capacity in a typical EV, that's days of backup power.
- **Solar self-consumption** — If you have [solar panels](/guides/ev-charger-solar-panels-uk/), V2H lets you store excess daytime generation in your car and use it in the evening — essentially using your EV as a giant home battery.

V2H avoids many of V2G's complications while still delivering meaningful savings. For homes with solar panels and a time-of-use tariff, the business case is already reasonable.

---

## Our Verdict: Is V2G Worth It in 2026?

**For most UK EV owners today: not yet.** The technology works, the trials are promising, and the economics will eventually stack up — but the combination of limited car compatibility, expensive chargers, and uncertain payback means V2G isn't a sensible purchase for the average household in 2026.

**For early adopters and solar-heavy households:** If you already have [solar panels](/guides/ev-charger-solar-panels-uk/), a compatible vehicle, and you're comfortable being on the leading edge, V2H (vehicle-to-home) makes a reasonable case today — especially if you're considering a [home battery](/guides/ev-charger-solar-panels-uk/) anyway.

**For everyone else:** Get a great [smart charger](/guides/smart-ev-charger-explained/) now — the [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/), [Zappi](/reviews/zappi-v2-review/), or [Hypervolt Home 3](/reviews/hypervolt-home-3-review/) — and switch to a [cheap off-peak tariff](/guides/best-ev-tariff-uk-2026/). These deliver guaranteed savings of £300–£500 per year today, with zero compatibility risk. When V2G matures (likely 2027–2028), you'll be well-positioned to upgrade.

The future of V2G in the UK is genuinely exciting. But the present is still about [smart one-directional charging](/best-picks/best-ev-charger-smart-tariff/) — and that's already excellent.

